Facebook & the Adobe Flash Platform Mixer
Mark went
Please join Facebook and Adobe for a night of pool, drinks, and learn more about the recently announced ActionScript 3.0 Cient Library for the Facebook Platform at Jillians on Thursday, April 2nd. Spend a relaxing evening with us and take advantage of interacting with the Facebook and Adobe Platform teams. The event starts at 6:30 pm at Jillians in the Metreon located near the Moscone Center. Learn more about the ActionScript 3 APIs from: *Ethan Beard (Facebook, Director of Platform) *Dave Story (Adobe, VP of Engineering) *Josh Elman (Facebook, Platform Program Manager) *Michael Graves (gskinner.com) *We have limited space so please arrive early to ensure your spot. First come, first served! Look forward to seeing you there! If you are unable to attend this special presentation, please join us for a free online eSeminar showcasing how Adobe’s Flash Platform is great for building Facebook apps. The event is on April 9th, and you can register by visiting: http://www.adobe.com/go/flex_seminars.
Thursday, April 2, 2009, 6:30 PM - 10:30 PM in PDT
Jillian's,101 Fourth Street,San Francisco,California,United States

A Toast to Sam: a reception following his memorial service
Mark Zuckerberg was invited
NOTE: this event page is only for the reception following the memorial service, which is being held just prior at 10AM at Beth Am, 26790 Arastradero Rd, Los Altos Hills, CA 94022. Dear friends: will be holding a reception immediately following the memorial service for our dear friend and colleague Sam Felder. Anyone and everyone is welcome to attend both the service and the reception. We are looking to get a rough count of attendees for the reception so we can plan enough food and drink, but please come whether or not you've had the chance to rsvp. We all want to be together to remember Sam. Looking forward to seeing you all. Please note that there will likely be special instructions on where to park near my house, so stay tuned for those details. xoxo
